# ComponentBuilderPython

## First time environment setup

To standardize across environments, [poetry](https://python-poetry.org/docs/basic-usage/) is used to track and manage Python dependencies. It manages virtual environments for you and resolves Python dependencies no matter what version of Python you're using.

1. Install Poetry: `pip3 install poetry`
2. Install project packages: `poetry install`
3. Run single-line commands within the environment: `poetry run <command>`, i.e: `poetry run python`
4. Open a shell in the environment: `poetry shell`

## Build and running tests

1. To activate the virtual environment: `poetry shell`
2. To build the project: `poetry build`. To build using the previous method of building: `poetry run python setup.py bdist_wheel`
   1. Before the next build ensure you clean up the previous build artifacts: `rm -rf build ComponentBuilderPython.egg-info`
3. Unittests should be written using [pytest](https://docs.pytest.org/en/7.1.x/). 
   1. To run all tests (Datasets and Instructions): `pytest` (or `poetry run pytest`)
   2. To run the manual suite: `pytest --runmanual`
   3. To run a specific test: `pytest test/cb/server/datasets/test_xlsx_format.py` 

